<p>I'm trying to apply a style to the label for a radiobutton with the CHECKED attribute, but everything I've tried fails to match on IE7.</p>  <p>Example (<a href="http://jsfiddle.net/fleb/jbh3nt95/" rel="nofollow">JSFiddle</a>):</p>  <pre><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; &lt;html&gt;     &lt;head&gt;         &lt;title&gt;Title&lt;/title&gt;         &lt;style type="text/css"&gt;             /* Ensure that + selectors work */             input + span { color: blue; }              /* Try [checked] alone */             input[checked] + span { color: red; }              /* Try selecting by value */             input[checked="checked"] + span { color: green; }         &lt;/style&gt;     &lt;/head&gt;     &lt;body&gt;         &lt;form&gt;             &lt;input type="radio" checked="checked" name="x" /&gt;&lt;span&gt;One&lt;/span&gt;             &lt;input type="radio" name="x" /&gt;&lt;span&gt;Two&lt;/span&gt;             &lt;input type="radio" name="x" /&gt;&lt;span&gt;Three&lt;/span&gt;         &lt;/form&gt;     &lt;/body&gt; &lt;/html&gt; </code></pre>  <p>All SPANs' text are blue, but the first one is neither red nor green, in IE7 (both native and emulated in IE11). Will I need JS hack-arounds, or is there some trick to the CSS that I can employ to get this working?</p>